                vulnerability assessment, and building secure web applications using modern .NET technologies. 
                I'm passionate about digital security and creating robust, secure software solutions.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-section">
            <h2>Education</h2>
            
            <div class="education-item">
                <h3>Bachelor of Science in Computer Science</h3>
                <p class="institution">Copperbelt University, Zambia</p>
                <p class="duration">Expected Graduation: 2028</p>
                <p class="description">
                    Pursuing a comprehensive computer science degree with focus on software engineering, algorithms, data structures, and modern programming paradigms. 
                    Coursework includes advanced topics in artificial intelligence, machine learning, database systems, and software architecture.
                </p>
                <ul class="achievements-list">
                    <li>Maintained Dean's List status for academic excellence</li>
                    <li>Active member of Computer Science Student Association</li>
                    <li>Participated in programming competitions and hackathons</li>
                    <li>Completed advanced coursework in software engineering and system design</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="education-item">
                <h3>Secondary School Certificate</h3>
                <p class="institution">Choma Secondary School, Zambia</p>
                <p class="duration">Graduated: 2022</p>
                <p class="description">
                    Completed secondary education with strong performance in mathematics, sciences, and computer studies. 
                    Developed foundational knowledge in analytical thinking and problem-solving that laid the groundwork for pursuing computer science.
                </p>
                <ul class="achievements-list">
                    <li>Graduated with distinction in Mathematics and Computer Studies</li>
                    <li>Served as class representative and peer tutor</li>
                    <li>Participated in inter-school science competitions</li>
